== Related Articles == * [[:en:Decapodiformes|Squid]] * [[:en:Port of Hakodate|Hakodate Port]] – Related to the Hakodate Port Festival and the aftermath of the [[:en:Great Fire of Hakodate|Great Fire of Hakodate]]. **''' {{ill|Hakodate Port Festival|ja|函館港まつり|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakodate Port Festival|qq=}} **''' {{ill|Sakamoto Moriichi|ja|坂本森一|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakamoto Moriichi|qq=}}, Hakodate mayor who initiated the port festival based on a proposal by maritime union leader Tanitokutaro. * Performance Locations: **''' {{ill|Jūjigai|ja|十字街 (函館市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jūjigai|qq=}} – {{ill|Daimon|ja|大門 (函館市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daimon|qq=}} – {{ill|Goryōkaku Area|ja|五稜郭地区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Goryōkaku Area|qq=}}, Hakodate’s entertainment district. **''' {{ill|Wakamatsu Wharf|ja|若松ふ頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakamatsu Wharf|qq=}}, the cruise terminal and former ferry dock. * {{ill|Ikanopolis Plan|ja|イカノポリス計画|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikanopolis Plan|qq=}}: A redevelopment concept for Hakodate after the closure of the {{ill|Seikan Ferry|ja|青函連絡船|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seikan Ferry|qq=}}, spearheaded by the {{ill|Hokkaido Small and Medium Business Association|ja|北海道中小企業家同友会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkaido Small and Medium Business Association|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. * {{ill|Hokkai Bon Odori|ja|北海盆踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkai Bon Odori|qq=}}: A related festival dance held by neighborhood associations during the port festival.
